  "explanation": "In determining the sentence for the defendant, the court considered both mitigating and aggravating factors. As a first-time offender who has already begun the restitution process, the defendant demonstrates a low risk of recidivism and a degree of remorse. However, the role of an accountant carries a high level of fiduciary responsibility, and the embezzlement of $25,000 represents a serious breach of professional trust. While the outburst from the spectator was entirely disregarded in this legal determination, a period of incarceration is necessary to reflect the gravity of the white-collar offense and to provide a just punishment. Consequently, a split sentence involving a short period of incarceration followed by probation is appropriate.",
  "verdict": 6
